I am giving 5 stars for the location on the top level thats  right by the train station. I frequent this location because I work in the building. Very good customer service, even if it’s crowded they always make my drinks and sandwiches in a timely manner. They are organized and know how to take care of the line and also get people in and out the door. Now this location should give a whole powerpoint presentation on ethics and customer service to the new location located on the lower level that is close to MAC. Since this location is closer to where I work, I frequent there when I go on break. Not ONCE have I had a positive experience, as all of my coworkers can vouch for. They always take FOREVER to do the simplest of things and aren’t respectful of your time. I once went there on my break to order a drink, the store was pretty empty. As I was waiting for my drink, the 2 baristas were just standing there chatting amongst themselves laughing. I had to stare at their direction for them to get the hint that I’m waiting. You can obviously make the assumption I was on break because of what I was wearing. As soon as they noticed I was staring at their direction that’s when they began to make my drink. There was absolutely no excuse for this, as it wasn’t even busy at all and I was on a time limit. Whenever I purchase anything that needs to be heated takes at least a minimum of 10 minutes. Today I was assisted disgracefully by one of the employees there that was short, wearing a black hat, had medium complexion and a pony tail. When I told her that I was waiting over 5 minutes for a simple bagel, she walked away from me, came back with the bagel that was all crumbled up and said condescendingly “It was 5 minutes, actually*” and walked away. She probably felt confident to speak in such a tone because she thought I was done receiving my order, which I wasn’t because I was waiting for a brownie which also took another while to come. She came back and I just said thank you and walked out. I told my coworkers of the behavior of this specific cast in this location and all of them had so many things to say about how negative their experiences were. One of my coworkers ordered online in advance and still had to wait 20 minutes in person to receive their order, which took the whole purpose away of ordering online. Another experience was when they took too long hearing up something so simple, which my coworker ended up speaking up about and was given a card with some credit in it for the inconvenience. She mentioned how her experience was sour every single time she visited the store. I work in customer service as well and things get much more hectic and we deal with all different kinds of clientele, and I can say they need a few pointers. I am respectful of everyone’s time, especially for those that work in the building. There are plenty of more occasions that I can mention, but point is either they need to hire new management, hire a whole new cast or have everyone attend a training as I said previously on ethics and customer service because they absolutely need it. It is a shame that they lost me as a customer along with a handful of people, we will no longer frequent there and we’ll proceed to go to the other location located on the upper level instead who have never ceased to give excellent customer service. If it wasn’t for the lower location not having their own review section, they’d get one star. This location is better off closed if they will continue to give this kind of service.
The working crew on this location is more proactive, prompt and customer attentive what else I would want from Starbucks when grabbing my latte on my way....
